tp://www.loc.gov/item/11693393", "http://www.loc.gov/item/97505202", "97505202"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["photo, print, drawing"], "partof": ["catalog", "prints & photographs online catalog (library of congress)", "prints and photographs division", "miscellaneous items in high demand"], "score": 26.151562, "shelf_id": "Illus. in AP2.H32 1875 (Case Y) [P&P]", "site": ["pictures", "catalog"], "subject": ["assistance", "red cloud", "periodical illustrations", "wood engravings", "nebraska", "indians of north america", "government relations"], "timestamp": "2022-05-02T12:58:13.452Z", "title": "An Indian agency - distributing rations", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/97505202/"}, {"access_restricted": true, "aka": ["https://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/91790903/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/91790903/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/91790903/", "https://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/coll/item/91790903/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/coll/item/91790903/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/91790903"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["miller, james a."], "date": "1909", "dates": ["1909"], "description": ["11 photographic prints : gelatin silver ; 17 x 10 cm. or smaller. | Six images relate to the filming of the movie, \"The Indian Wars,\" on Pine Ridge Reservation in 1913. Depicted are an Indian encampment at  Wounded Knee, U.S. troops surrounding the encampment, and Buffalo Bill, the main consultant for the film, with Major Brennan. Also includes two images of Dakota in Gordon, Nebraska; one showing an encampment at the Gordon Fair, and the other of Dakota men in feather headdresses. Included are portraits of Oglala Chief Red Cloud with his son Jack Red Cloud, and a woman, possibly Red Cloud's granddaughter; Jack Red Cloud, and Chief American Horse."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-03-07T14:04:29.201Z", "group": ["coll", "catalog-split-06", "catalog", "groups-of-images", "main-catalog-split-06"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://w